==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Abolition
<hw>Ab"o*li"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>abolitio</ets>, fr. <ets>abolere</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>abolition</ets>. See <er>Abolish</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of
abolishing, or the state of being abolished; an annulling; abrogation;
utter destruction; <as>as, the <ex>abolition</ex> of slavery or the
slave trade; the <ex>abolition</ex> of laws, decrees, ordinances,
customs, taxes, debts, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The application of this word to persons is now unusual
or obsolete</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>abolitionary</ent>⟦br⟧
